(numRXQEntries, numRXQEntries).explanation: A variable cannot cause itself as this would be circular and logically impossible;

(numRXQEntries, CPI).explanation: Increasing the number of RXQ entries allows more memory requests to be buffered, reducing memory-related stalls and improving instruction throughput, thereby decreasing CPI;

(numRXQEntries, nICacheWays).explanation: RXQ entries are part of the memory subsystem while instruction cache associativity is a separate cache design parameter with no direct causal relationship;
